{"id":"mashal","term":"Mashal","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Entreaty, a levitical town in the tribe of Asher (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 6:74\">1 Chr. 6:74</a>); called Mishal (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 21:30\">Josh. 21:30</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Chronicles 6:74","Joshua 21:30"]}